<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col col-med-6">
      <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading">
          <div class="panel-title heading">
            <h2>Create a new Venue</h2>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-body">
          <%= form_for @venue do |f| %>
          <div>
            <%= label_tag "select an organization to manage booking at this venue:" %>
            <%= select_tag 'organization_id', options_for_select(@orgs.map {|o| [o.name, o.id]}) %>
          </div>
          <div>
            <%= f.label :venue_name %>
            <%= f.text_field :name, required: true %>
          </div>
          <div>
            <%= f.label :hooks %>
            <%= f.text_field :hooks %>
            <a data-toggle="modal" data-target="#hooksHelp">what's this?</a>
          </div>
          <div>
            <%= f.label :location %>
            <%= f.text_field :location, required: true %>
          </div>
          <%= f.submit %>
          <% end %>
        </div>
        <div class="modal fade" id="hooksHelp" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="hooksHelpLabel" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="modal-dialog">
            <div class="modal-content">
              <div class="modal-header">
                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
                <h4 class="modal-title" id="hooksHelpLabel">What are hooks?:</h4>
              </div>
              <div class="modal-body">
                <p>
                  Note: if you don't plan to sync with google calendar you can leave this blank. You can also fill it out later.
                </p>
                <p>
                  ShiftSlot can sync with Google Calendar. One of the things that makes this possible are hooks. A hook is a piece of text that this app will look for when syncing with google calendar so that it can automatically infer what venue a show is booked at.
                </p>
                <p>
                  A hook can be any piece of text that might be associated with a venue. ShiftSlot will first check the title, and if that isn't found in the google calendar event it will then look for hooks.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Hooks are useful in the case of your organization using a google calendar for booking shows prior to using this app.
                </p>
                <h4>Example:</h4>
                - fill in example here before deploy -
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
